3. Question: did they build ships for pirates of the caribbean
   Answer: True, because In the first movie, the Black Pearl was a steel barge with wooden structures built on top to resemble a real ship. 7. Question: is the vice president the head of the senate
Answer:  False, because The Vice President of the United States is not the President of the Senate, although the Vice President does preside over the Senate when it is in session, and has the power to vote in the Senate only in the event of a tie. The Vice President is also an ex officio member of every committee of the Senate, and may participate in its deliberations. The Vice President is not a member of the Senate, and is not considered a senator for any purpose.
 Text:As the Senate president, the vice president presides over its deliberations (or delegates this task to a member of the Senate), but is allowed to vote only when it is necessary to break a tie. While this vote-casting prerogative has been exercised chiefly on legislative issues, it has also been used to break ties on the election of Senate officers, as well as on the appointment of Senate committees. In this capacity, the vice president also presides over joint sessions of Congress. 
   Answer: 
   The Vice President does not preside over the Senate as its head, but rather presides over its sessions and has the power to vote in the event of a tie. The President of the Senate is a largely ceremonial role.

7. Question: is there goal line technology in the world cup
Answer: 
Yes, since 2014 FIFA World Cup, goal line technology has been used in the FIFA World Cup. The technology uses multiple cameras that monitor the goal line and can detect whether the ball has completely crossed the goal line. The referee is alerted if the ball has crossed the line, and the video assistant referee (VAR) confirms the decision. The technology was developed to reduce errors in determining whether a goal should be awarded or not.
 Text:Compared to similar technology in other sports, goal-line technology is a relatively recent addition to association football; its integration having been opposed by the sport's authorities. In July 2012, the International Football Association Board (IFAB) officially approved the use of goal line technology, amending the Laws of the Game to permit (but not require) its use. Due to its expense, goal-line technology is only used at the highest levels of the game. Goal-line technology is currently used in the top European domestic leagues, and at major international competitions such as the 2014 Men's, 2018 Men's and 2015 Women's FIFA World Cups. 
   Answer: The text states that goal-line technology was approved by the International Football Association Board (IFAB) in July 2012 and is used in the top European domestic leagues and major international competitions such as the FIFA World Cup.
